  <original-body>Currently, when you generate a new scaffold, the generated controller tests are calling `.id` on a fixture like so:

@@@ ruby
def test_should_get_show
  get :show, :id =&gt; articles(:one).id
end
@@@

Since `to_param` is the canonical thing to pass, we should generate tests that conform to this standard:

@@@ ruby
def test_should_get_show
  get :show, :id =&gt; articles(:one).to_param
end
@@@

This will lead to fewer broken tests after something as trivial as a slug change.</original-body>
